results.name: If n is 1 or a prime, then a(n) = 1, otherwise a(n) = the third smallest divisor of n.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: If A020639(n)^2 divides n [when n is in A283050] and either A119288(n) = 1 or A020639(n)^2 < A119288(n), then a(n) = A020639(n)^2, otherwise a(n) = A119288(n).
program: (Scheme) (define (A292269 n) (let ((x (A000290 (A020639 n))) (y (A119288 n))) (if (and (zero? (modulo n x)) (or (= 1 y) (< x y))) x y)))
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Oct 04 2017
